    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-11T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-11T08:00:00-05:00" n="451"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">760C.60K/123: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Danzig</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Danzig</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-11T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 11, 1931—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 11—10:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The High Commissioner of the League of Nations informs me during the past few
                    weeks he has received from the Polish Commissioner General a number of
                    complaints concerning alleged physical attacks on Polish citizens in most cases
                    by members of Hitler party. Danzig police have made no arrests and have denied
                    most of the Polish allegations. Polish Commissioner General demands protection
                    of Polish citizens. The High Commissioner considers the situation most serious.
                        <pb facs="0710" n="596" xml:id="pg_596"/> He has obtained promise of a
                    thorough investigation from the President of the Senate and has suggested that a
                    committee composed of the American, British and the Belgian Consuls be asked to
                    investigate incidents in which Danzig and Poland cannot agree as to the facts.
                    This suggestion will be submitted to the Senate and the Polish Government. Am I
                    authorized to accept an invitation to serve from the High Commissioner?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
